  "texts": [
    "This discriminatory ability was expected, as the neuropsychological tests forming the composites are partially instrumental in defining the diagnoses.",
    "Nevertheless, these results show that their grouping into cognitive domains is consistent and effectively summarizes the information from the individual neuropsychological tests into higher cognitive functions.",
    "Therefore, this subanalysis supports the use of these neuropsychological groupings to describe the different cognitive functions analyzed.The algorithms used to infer the neurocognitive composites based on the SS tests and physical-acoustic features showed a strong predictive ability (Fig. 4).",
    "In general, we observed that the models were proficient in predicting the different cognitive scores with a correlation close to 0.5 relative to the actual values (Table 4).",
    "Nevertheless, our findings indicated a significant increase in model errors within the SCD and ADD groups."
  ]
}